Process called "combine_xyz_data" that takes x as NDArray.NDArray and y as NDArray.NDArray and z as NDArray.NDArray returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let n_points be Math.min with a as x.size and b as Math.min with a as y.size and b as z.size
    Let combined be NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing n_points, 3 For i from 0 to n_points - 1:
    Set combined.data at index (i multiplied by 3) to x.data at index i
    Set combined.data at index (i multiplied by 3 1) to y.data at index i
    Set combined.data at index (i multiplied by 3 2) to z.data at index i Return combined

Process called "calculate_contour_levels" that takes z as NDArray.NDArray and n_levels as Integer returns List[Float]:
    Let min_z be calculate_array_min with array as z
    Let max_z be calculate_array_max with array as z
    Let levels be list containing For i from 0 to n_levels - 1:
    Let level be min_z Float.from with value as i multiplied by (max_z - min_z) divided by Float.from with value as (n_levels - 1)
    Add level to levels Return levels

Process called "calculate_moving_average" that takes prices as NDArray.NDArray and period as Integer and ma_type as String returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let ma_data be NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing (prices.size - period 1) For i from period - 1 to prices.size - 1:
    Let sum be 0.0
    For j from (i - period 1) to i:
    Set sum to sum Float.from with value as prices.data at index j
    Set ma_data.data at index (i - period 1) to sum divided by Float.from with value as period Return ma_data

